message:
v7.0.2

- patch compatibility with "Web Components" classes
- patch mounting portals
- patch clone element

v7.0.3

- handle invalid values for `style` prop

v7.0.4

- bypass `shouldComponentUpdate` when coming from `forceUpdate`.
- patch `Components` to not require passing props to `super()`.
- patch missing value in `DOM` attributes that use the primitve `true` value.

v7.1.0

- Allow lazy loading primitive to render while loading module.
- Improve Promise return types.
push work on dio-V8 to github

- pass additional arguments to events: props & state.
- improve server render implementation.
- remove `undefined` or `false` style object values.
- general improvements.

- improve PureComponent's shouldComponentUpdate shallow compare.
- generate esm module bundle
- add esm module path to package.json

- patch componentWillUnmount lifecycle execution.
- improve async componentWillUnmount.
- call component refs with null when unmounting.
- improve PureComponent shallow compare.
generate .min/.map versions for esm and node as well

- move test setup to mocha + chai
- improve tests
- add more tests

minor optimizations

1.  [Reconciler] Equality check before diff to short circuit an
otherwise no-op diff.
2. [package.json] Remove unpkg field from package since that points to
the `main` build anyway.
3. [Children.toArray] Use .forEach property check to potentially
support other types of iterables that might be unknown at the time but
supply a forEach method.
4. [Docs] Add jsdelivr as a CDN option.

- improve error boundaries to closely resemble react error boundaries
- handle recursive errors in error boundaries
- more tests

- 🎉 100% test coverage.

- Improve dangerouslySetInnerHTML.

	How should this work? We can follow react and warn when it's used together with children
	or handle it how this commit handles it, by allowing these two namespaces
	dangerouslySetInnerHTML and children to coexist.

- Prevent direct `innerHTML` use.

	Mitigate accidental/malicious intent when spreading props which might have innerHTML injected.

- Improve DOM renderer abstraction.

- improve reconciler
- better handle children as props pattern
- always convert `tabIndex` attribute to lowercase in server render
- handle recursive error in error boundaries
- insure root node is passed to componentWillUnmount lifecycle
- more tests
- React Parity, make setState from componentDidMount register synchronously

- add guard to insure spoofing a server enviroment in a non server enviroment doesn't break exports
- add tests for rendering to fragment and handling duplicate keys
prerelease chore: update package.json and CHANGELOG

- It's not major release unless you forget some small detail :)
	seems like dio.version was pointing to '8.0.0-beta-1' when it should be "8.0.0"

v8.0.2

- reflect setState calls from componentWillReceiveProps lifecycle to update state synchronously like React.

v8.0.3

- patch error when used with brunch, fusebox and browserfy bundlers.
initial work on 8.1.0 create custom renderer package

- add instrumentation tests for reconcile DOM operations.
- use global Symbol for `dio.Fragment` API.
- improve reconciling moves.

- improve handling of object properties.
- improve examples.
- reduce implementation details of setDOMProps further.
- minor improvement to the implementation details of assigning object props.

- improve treatment of static elements.
- other implementation detail improvments.

- insure dynamic mutation of render method is always allowed.

	transpilers might emmit this pattern when transpiling classes.

- improve typescript definitions.
- minor improve to reconciler operation count on one worst-case edge case.

- add changelog entry.
- fix sourcemap paths in package.json.
- bump version.

v8.2.1

- patch order of calling component ref when unmounting.
- patch server side rendering, call to `componentWillMount` lifecycle.

v8.2.2

- patch async setState in `componentWillMount` lifecycle to work on server-side renderer.

v8.2.3

- patch children props sementics when coupled with both children props and children elements to behave like React and prefer children elements instead of the accumulation of both.

- separate context tests from component tests in prep for new context API.
AsyncGenerator: pass previous value to yield

2nd alpha release

- Improve both context implementation.
- Improve unmount implementation.
- Pass host element to custom reconcilers willUnmount method.

9.0.0 beta

- Handle circular references in props.
- Improve jsdocs.

9.0.0 release candidate

- Revert to previous context implementation that does not rely on the
old context API to ensure both API’s can co-exist, related:
https://github.com/facebook/react/issues/12551#issuecomment-378924725

- Support `defaultValue` on select elements.

- Fix getChildContext’s update phase invocation to happen after state
has updated but before “render”.

Second release candidate

- Error: Only force unmount if an ErrorBoundary has not caught the error this is motivated by how well this will work with future work on a Suspense API and the use cases that @Zolmeister previously mentioned in 8.0.0.
- Tests: Move all ref related tests to a dedicated ref spec file.
- Ref: Improve ref implementation.
- Render: only set defaultValue for the select elements on initial mount.
- Reconciler: Expose a signature argument to `setProps` that reconcilers can use to determine the phase at which the method is being invoked in.
- Reconciler: Pass the container as an argument to `getPortal`.

Third Release Candidate

- Improve select defaultValue implementation.
- Improve Children.toArray implementation.
- Support multiple event handlers on a single event.
- Add Todo and Custom Elements examples to docs.

Pre release candidate

- Patch ErrorBoundary bug with interleaved corrupted children.
- Improve documentation.
- Remove some indirection related to server renderer and error boundaries
#72 - enhancements to build scripts and test scripts (separate DEV and PROD packages)
#72 - fixed nyc issues and added header to test output

- Add eslint(devDependency) for liniting.
- Add esm(devDependency) for node esm modules.

- Improve architecture to allow for effectively scheduling low priority
updates when needed.

- Simplify error boundaries logic.

- Remove some legacy API’s.

- Setup testing infrastructure wth ism modules.
- Improve commit dispatch mechanic from an event.

- Improve scheduler.
- Allow thenables a “timeout” prop.
- Allow any props on portal(vs only key).
- Lay foundations for supporting re-parting with portals.
- Add mores tests(Component, Render, Comment, etc…).
- Improve fallback Promise implementation.

- Improve reconciler.
- Add reconciler tests.
- Use constructor instead of pojo for element shapes.

Support awaitables on render, setState and forceUpdate

- Insure the parity of Element.from is constant, since Array.map passes
three arguments. Apply the same sementic to to dyo.Children helpers.

- Add generic server renderer.
- Improve interface abstraction.
